  "title": "QA Analyst (UAT) - Insurance (1 Year contract)",
  "description": "<p><ul><li>Develop comprehensive test plans and test cases based on business, functional, and system requirements for digital platforms.</li><li>Coordinate test plan reviews with business and technology stakeholders, ensuring timely feedback, alignment, and formal sign-off.</li><li>Execute test cases accurately, document results, and ensure traceability to approved requirements.<br />Identify, log, and track defects throughout the testing lifecycle; work closely with development teams to support resolution and retesting.</li><li>Maintain clear and structured testing documentation, including execution records, defect logs, and retest outcomes.</li><li>Communicate testing progress, risks, and issues to stakeholders, providing transparency on release readiness.</li><li>Support User Acceptance Testing (UAT) and obtain final sign-off to ensure solutions meet agreed acceptance criteria prior to production release.</li></ul></p><p>Interested applicants please send your resume in MS Word format and attention it to Rachel Yeo (R22104385).</p><p>Shortlisted candidates will be notified</p><p>Data provided is for recruitment purposes only</p><p>www.ambition.com.sg</p><p>EA Registration Number: R22104385</p><p>Business Registration Number: 200611680D. Licence Number: 10C5117</p>",
